Cool post, Frank R.

I would agree with &quot;of the light,&quot; yet I know those who are of the 
light also bring light (truth, love) to others.  Light is never 
overcome by darkness; darkness ceases to exist when light shines upon 
it.  Darkness is therefore better described as &quot;lost&quot; or &quot;illusion.&quot;  
It is therefore truth that shines in and frees those whose condition 
needs it.  Fear would be darkness...lack of understanding.  It is 
false and only has power when given it.

I like the quote Frank R., as there is a big difference 
between &quot;belief&quot; and &quot;knowing.&quot; &quot;Knowing&quot; is knowledge of the 
truth. &quot;Knowing&quot; is power and produces action, change, results, 
etc; &quot;belief&quot; or &quot;faith&quot; is only hoping something to be true.  

